{"_id":"AoHGMvFoA08aEVwI","name":"Attack","type":"move","img":"icons/svg/lightning.svg","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>When you use a weapon to attack, select a target, or targets, valid for the weapon, and roll +VIO. Refer to the weapon for any additional requirements.</p>\n<p>To determine damage, roll a d6, applying any bonuses or penalties, and look up the result in the weapon's damage table. Treat any value below 1 as 1. NPCs take damage the same way that PCs do.</p>","choices":null,"moveType":"basic","rollFormula":"","moveResults":{"failure":{"value":"<p>After the GM explains the consequences, describe why whatever happened is not your fault. If your scapegoat is another PC, or if blame-shifting is not applicable, gain 1 XP Point.</p>"},"partial":{"value":"<p>Choose one:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>You attack recklessly or aggressively, opening yourself up to attack or an environmental hazard.</li>\n<li>You attack defensively, and subtract 1 from the weapon's damage lookup roll.</li>\n<li>You have to fire several shots (e.g. blind-firing, aggressive self-cover fire), reducing your ammo by 1.</li>\n<li>You suffer a setback.</li>\n</ul>"},"success":{"value":"<p>You deal the weapon's damage to the enemy.</p>\n<p>You may choose one of the options below to add 1 to the weapon's damage lookup roll:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>You attack recklessly or aggressively, opening yourself up to attack or an environmental hazard.</li>\n<li>You attack defensively, and subtract 1 from the weapon's damage lookup roll.</li>\n<li>You have to fire several shots (e.g. blind-firing, aggressive self-cover fire), reducing your ammo by 1.</li>\n<li>You suffer a setback.</li>\n</ul>"}},"class":"","rollType":"VIO","rollMod":0,"requiresLevel":0,"requiresMove":"","moveGroup":""},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"B6JUP195R7VugrMZ","name":"Aid or Interfere","type":"move","img":"icons/svg/hazard.svg","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>When you <strong>help or hinder someone you have a Bond</strong> with, roll+Bond with them. If you help, spend 1 XP Point.</p>","choices":"","moveType":"basic","rollFormula":"","moveResults":{"failure":{"value":"<p>After the GM explains the consequences, describe why whatever happened is not your fault. If your scapegoat is another PC, or if blame-shifting is not applicable, gain 1 XP Point.</p>"},"partial":{"value":"<p>You also expose yourself to danger, retribution, or cost.</p>"},"success":{"value":"<p>They take +1 or -2, your choice.</p>"}},"class":"","rollType":"BOND","rollMod":0,"requiresLevel":0,"requiresMove":"","moveGroup":""},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EMiPGKem2NHxkMG3","name":"Your Number's Up","type":"move","img":"icons/svg/bones.svg","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>When your <strong>Harm level reaches Killed or Vaporized</strong>:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>If you don't have any spare clones, make a new character (and stop reading these steps).</li>\n<li>Mark an XP if you have not done so in the chain of events that lead to your demise.</li>\n<li>Increase your Clone Number by 1.</li>\n<li>You may Level Up as though you had downtime.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>The GM will tell you what happens next.</p>","choices":"","moveType":"special","rollFormula":"","moveResults":{"failure":{"value":null},"partial":{"value":null},"success":{"value":null}},"class":"","rollType":"","rollMod":0,"requiresLevel":0,"requiresMove":"","moveGroup":""},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"LzHIwZPj0TRyH0kD","name":"End of Session","type":"move","img":"icons/svg/door-exit.svg","data":{"name":"","description":"<p><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-26706950-7fff-960f-bb6b-7dec4318fa82\" style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">When you <strong>reach the end of a session:</strong></span></p>\n<ol>\n<li><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-26706950-7fff-960f-bb6b-7dec4318fa82\" style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">If you have fulfilled your Mandatory Bonus Duty, mark XP.</span></li>\n<li><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-26706950-7fff-960f-bb6b-7dec4318fa82\" style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">If you suggested a setback that contributed to the demise of another PC, mark XP.</span></li>\n<li><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-26706950-7fff-960f-bb6b-7dec4318fa82\" style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">If the session did not involve a Mission Debrief, The Computer will conduct an extemporaneous debriefing, and ask the team for reports of traitorous activity.</span></li>\n</ol>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">If The Computer <strong>conducts an extemporaneous debriefing</strong>:</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-26706950-7fff-960f-bb6b-7dec4318fa82\" style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">If anyone can identify a traitor and provide sufficient evidence to The Computer, The Computer will grant appropriate rewards.</span></li>\n<li><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-26706950-7fff-960f-bb6b-7dec4318fa82\" style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">If nobody has identified any traitors, The Computer will find the entire team to be traitors.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-26706950-7fff-960f-bb6b-7dec4318fa82\" style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">No dice are rolled. Anyone firing a laser weapon or using a mutant power acts as though their dice roll totaled to 10. Anyone doing any other move acts as though their dice totaled up to 7.</span></p>","choices":"","moveType":"special","rollFormula":"","moveResults":{"failure":{"value":""},"partial":{"value":""},"success":{"value":""}},"class":"","rollType":"","rollMod":0,"requiresLevel":0,"requiresMove":"","moveGroup":""},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"MpP7UucLeiYHaMK9","name":"Take Damage","type":"move","img":"icons/svg/explosion.svg","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>When you take damage, set your Harm level equal to the incoming damage. If this did not cause your Harm to increase, increase it by one step, but not past Killed.</p>\n<p>When you reach Maimed for the first time, the damage alters your character's body. The GM will tell you how.</p>","choices":"","moveType":"basic","rollFormula":"","moveResults":{"failure":{"value":""},"partial":{"value":""},"success":{"value":""}},"class":"","rollType":"","rollMod":0,"requiresLevel":0,"requiresMove":"","moveGroup":""},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"MrFHslXhzxGqjCJ1","name":"Regain Composure","type":"move","img":"icons/svg/regen.svg","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>When you've had a moment without any active threats to your well-being, reduce your Harm level from Snafued to Okay.</p>","choices":"","moveType":"basic","rollFormula":"","moveResults":{"failure":{"value":""},"partial":{"value":""},"success":{"value":""}},"class":"","rollType":"","rollMod":0,"requiresLevel":0,"requiresMove":"","moveGroup":""},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"ffsr8YYj4K3ljJWG","name":"Encumbrance","type":"move","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>When you <strong>make a move while carrying weight up to or equal to Load</strong>, youâ€™re fine.</p> <p>When you make a move while carrying weight equal to load+1 or load+2, you take -1.</p> <p>When you make a move while carrying weight greater than load+2, you have a choice: drop at least 1 weight and roll at -1, or automatically fail.</p>","choices":"","moveType":"special","rollFormula":"","moveResults":{"failure":{"value":null},"partial":{"value":""},"success":{"value":""}},"class":"","rollType":"","rollMod":0,"requiresLevel":0,"requiresMove":"","moveGroup":""},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"hCRRvZd7l65Fnfsv","name":"Unknown","type":"move","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>When you need to roll dice for a move, but the modifier doesn't fit, use this move instead. Enter the fully-adjusted modifier at the prompt.</p>","choices":"","moveType":"special","rollFormula":"","moveResults":{"failure":{"value":"<p>See the original move's 6- result.</p>"},"partial":{"value":"<p>See the original move's 7-9 result.</p>"},"success":{"value":"<p>See the original move's 10+ result.</p>"}},"class":"","rollType":"ASKMOD","rollMod":0,"requiresLevel":0,"requiresMove":"","moveGroup":""},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"pHv8C6GgXGORNh0p","name":"Suffer a Setback","type":"move","img":"icons/svg/falling.svg","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>When you suffer a setback, the GM chooses another Player, who then chooses one of the following side effects apropos to the situation:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>You receive a call from The Computer, or other official.</li>\n<li><span style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\">There are witnesses, or a camera, that notice/record the action.</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\">You are Snafued, or an item you are carrying or interacting with is damaged.</span></li>\n<li>An item malfunctions: see list of setbacks for the item.</li>\n<li>Another effect of similar magnitude to the ones above.</li>\n</ul>","choices":"","moveType":"basic","rollFormula":"","moveResults":{"failure":{"value":""},"partial":{"value":""},"success":{"value":""}},"class":"","rollType":"","rollMod":0,"requiresLevel":0,"requiresMove":"","moveGroup":""},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"qCutsQ8qGUmruv1X","name":"Defy Danger","type":"move","img":"icons/svg/shield.svg","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>When you act despite an imminent threat, or suffer a calamity, say how you deal with it and roll. If you do it:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Through bureacracy or fast talking, roll +MAN.</li>\n<li>By avoiding detection, roll +STL.</li>\n<li>Through physical avoidance or endurance, roll +VIO.</li>\n<li>By pushing buttons or turning dials, roll +HWR.</li>\n<li>Through adept typing, roll +SWR.</li>\n<li>By self-medicating, roll +WWR.</li>\n</ul>","choices":"","moveType":"basic","rollFormula":"","moveResults":{"failure":{"value":"<p>After the GM explains the consequences, describe why whatever happened is not your fault. If your scapegoat is another PC, or if blame-shifting is not applicable, gain 1 XP Point.</p>"},"partial":{"value":"<p>You stumble, hesitate, or flinch. The GM will offer you a worse outcome, hard bargain, or ugly choice.</p>"},"success":{"value":"<p>You do what you set out to do, and the threat doesn't come to bear.</p>"}},"class":"","rollType":"ASK","rollMod":0,"requiresLevel":0,"requiresMove":"","moveGroup":""},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
